{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"952ee3db-a2e7-46cb-8313-d4e81f7c75de","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, and tasks.md under specrunner/changes/evidence-authorship-enforcement/ on branch change/evidence-authorship-enforcement-b9b17b77. The plan implements ADR-20260718's evidence-authorship invariant via: (D1) authorship separation — sequential per-node commit excludes pipelineManagedPaths (events.jsonl/state.json/usage.json) and the pipeline commits the journal in a separate commit (+ round-end sweep); (D2) an in-process anchor built by accumulating pipeline-authored bytes (never read-back, avoiding a TOCTOU laundering window), seeded once on resume; (D3) a durable anchor blob at refs/specrunner/evidence/<branch> pushed at commitFinalState (agent-unreachable, crash-surviving); (D4) per-node verification of committed-tree journal-diff-empty + on-disk==in-process anchor with restore-then-halt; (D5) resume verification against the origin anchor with restore-from-origin; (D6) an attach authenticity predicate in verifyCheckpoint; (D7) unified fail-closed/absent-anchor rules with a safety-justified pre-branch/pre-feature skip; (D8) the accepted crash-recovery window. tasks.md sequences pure foundations → journal integration → authorship separation → per-path wiring, and names the T1–T8 adversarial/regression teeth (with 破壊確認 on the T1/T3 teeth). All planning only — no src/ edits; downstream implementer executes.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-19T00:18:55.960Z","endedAt":"2026-07-19T00:46:39.135Z","commitOid":"ac134a9d46258cd4fd79d8f8eb90b2bd30df94d4"}
